Step 1. Determine Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity from the Balance Sheet.  
• Total Current Liabilities = 378850.51  
• Total Owner’s Equity = 13835266.51  
Since no other liabilities are given, we take:  
 Total Liabilities = 378850.51

Step 2. Compute Debt to Equity Ratio  
 Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Owner’s Equity  
 = 378850.51 / 13835266.51  
 ≈ 0.02738  
Rounded to two decimal places, this is approximately 0.03.

Step 3. Compute Net Profit Margin using the Income Statement  
Net Profit = 835266.51  
Total Revenue = 2637011.03  
 Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) * 100  
 = (835266.51 / 2637011.03) * 100  
 ≈ 31.68%

Step 4. Compute Return on Assets (ROA)  
Total Assets (end) = 14214117.02  
 ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) * 100  
 = (835266.51 / 14214117.02) * 100  
 ≈ 5.88%

Step 5. Compute Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
The formula uses average accounts receivable.  
• Beginning Accounts Receivable = 0.00  
• Ending Accounts Receivable = 2117339.65  
 Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 2117339.65) / 2  
  = 1058669.825  
Now, using Main Business Revenue = 2637011.03, the ratio is:  
 Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
 = 2637011.03 / 1058669.825  
 ≈ 2.49

Thus, the final solution is:
